						<div class="postbody">I agree about working with consoles. The hardware is usually mostly the same (modulo, say, RAM bumps in later PSP models), and the libraries are much fewer making choosing easier. Not having to compensate for different screen resolutions in full screen, or RAM differences or OS differences, or processor speed differences is so freeing.
<br />
<br /> Even now that I'm capable of making PC games, I'd still prefer PSP. As for PC development being faster than NES, sure. But it's probably around the same speed as any other platform you can compile C for.</div>

