						<div class="postbody">$4301 isn't just the <em>starting</em> location, <em>every</em> byte in the DMA block get sent to that address, so DMA only does anything useful to registers $2104, $2118 and $2122.  All three have there own corrisponding address register, so why don't they just combine all three and cut out the middle man?</div>

